<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1830] Avro-Perl DataFileReader chokes when avro.codec is absent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1830</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a container does not specify its &quot;avro.codec&quot;, it should be assumed to be &quot;null&quot;. An exception is thrown when I try to read such a container using Avro::DataFileReader. The error happens at Avro/DataFileReader.pm line 101.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12959135">AVRO-1830</key>
            <summary>Avro-Perl DataFileReader chokes when avro.codec is absent</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="10002" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/document.png" description="A patch for this issue has been uploaded to JIRA by a contributor.">Patch Available</status>
                    <statusCategory id="4" key="indeterminate" colorName="yellow"/>
                                    <resolution id="-1">Unresolved</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="skliew">SK Liew</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Fri, 15 Apr 2016 10:57:02 +0000</created>
                <updated>Sat, 16 Apr 2016 00:27:24 +0000</updated>
                                            <version>1.8.0</version>
                                                    <component>perl</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15242810" author="skliew" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 11:10:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a patch which is to set $codec to &quot;null&quot; when &quot;avro.codec&quot; does not exist in a container&apos;s metadata.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243168" author="rdblue" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 16:19:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=_alexm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;_alexm&quot;&gt;Alex Moundalexis&lt;/a&gt;, are you still up for reviewing perl patches?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243181" author="_alexm" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 16:30:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s no NULL in Perl. You&apos;d want to use &lt;a href=&quot;http://perldoc.perl.org/functions/defined.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;undef&lt;/a&gt; instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243186" author="_alexm" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 16:34:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://perldoc.perl.org/functions/undef.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;undef&lt;/a&gt;, rather:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;my $codec = $data-&amp;gt;{meta}{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;avro.codec&apos;&lt;/span&gt;} || undef;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243206" author="_alexm" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 16:48:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A little concerning that &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/avro/blob/master/lang/perl/t/04_datafile.t#L64&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;tests&lt;/a&gt; are checking for a string of &quot;null&quot; instead of undef.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243209" author="skliew" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2016 16:49:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &apos;null&apos; here refers to a valid codec. $data-&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
{meta}{&apos;avro.codec&apos;} || undef would set $codec to undef when $data-&amp;gt;{meta}
{&apos;avro.codec&apos;}
&lt;p&gt; is undef, which would still fail the is_codec_valid test:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
our %ValidCodec = (&lt;br/&gt;
    null    =&amp;gt; 1,&lt;br/&gt;
    deflate =&amp;gt; 1,&lt;br/&gt;
);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sub is_codec_valid {&lt;br/&gt;
    my $datafile = shift;&lt;br/&gt;
    my $codec = shift || &apos;&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
    return $ValidCodec{$codec};&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15243897" author="skliew" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2016 00:27:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The Avro 1.8.0 specification states that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All metadata properties that start with &quot;avro.&quot; are reserved. The following file metadata properties are currently used:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;avro.schema contains the schema of objects stored in the file, as JSON data (required).&lt;br/&gt;
avro.codec the name of the compression codec used to compress blocks, as a string. Implementations are required to support the following codecs: &quot;null&quot; and &quot;deflate&quot;. If codec is absent, it is assumed to be &quot;null&quot;. The codecs are described with more detail below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To implement the requirement above, in the case when it is not defined (when avro.codec is not specified in metadata, and that&apos;s when $data-&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
{meta}
{&apos;avro.codec&apos;}
&lt;p&gt; is undef), I think it should default to the string &quot;null&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
