<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1831] Take advantage of JSR 3.5 annotations in the generated java classes.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1831</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;it would be nice if the generated records would take advantage of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@javax.annotation.Nullable&lt;br/&gt;
@javax.annotation.Nonnull&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to annotate the fields that can be null...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would have a documenting role, and more importantly allow windbags to detect incorrect use of the fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
